# Keep the Docker build context small and free of host-specific artifacts.
# This is critical: host node_modules (e.g. Windows binaries) must NOT be
# copied into the Linux image, and build outputs are regenerated inside Docker.

# Dependencies (reinstalled inside the image)
**/node_modules

# Build outputs / caches (rebuilt inside the image)
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local env files (provide these via Railway variables instead)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Version control & editor
.git
.gitignore
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# Logs & OS files
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Runtime/session data that must never be baked into the image
**/sessions
**/baileys_auth
**/uploads
